Sentencas: La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-delta (LSM) magnetic properties are exploited through the application of a magnetic field, resulting in a significant decrease of the cathode polarization resistance, a crucial component of high temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes

Sentencas: The magnetic field is applied during the drying process after the deposition of LSM cathodes by screen-printing on a Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (GDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes

Sentencas: This specific process aims to decrease the cathode polarization resistance of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction patterns show a structural modification triggered by the magnetic field.
Titulo: Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes

Sentencas: LSM cathode performance is investigated over a temperature range of 700-800 degrees C by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes

Sentencas: The measured electrode area specific resistance (ASR) of a LSM/GDC/LSM symmetric half-cell without and with magnetic field was 0.30 Omega cm(2) and 0.20 Omega cm(2), respectively, at 800 degrees C. The ASR value was therefore decreased by 33% with the magnetic field effect.
Titulo: Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes

Sentencas: This behaviour may be attributed to LSM grain reorientation, microstructure change, and tortuosity modification of LSM cathodes.
Titulo: Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes
Magnetic field effect on the electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-δ cathodes
